    • Constructor Detail

      • Goomba

        public Goomba(javafx.scene.Group parent,
              GameLoop gameLoop,
              Mario mario,
              int stageZone,
              boolean checkBlockCollision,
              java.lang.String[] SVGData,
              float xPos,
              float yPos,
              float xVel,
              float yVel,
              javafx.scene.image.Image[] playerDeathSprites,
              javafx.scene.image.Image... sprites)
        Constructs a single Goomba enemy at specified location in stage.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent in which which the Goomba should reside.
        gameLoop - An instance of GameLopp class. Used to stop the main loop upon death of player (Mario).
        mario - The player (Mario). Used to check various interactions and play resultant logic.
        stageZone - Stage zone in which the Goomba resides. See class StageFloorBase.
        checkBlockCollision - Will this enemy collide with StageBlocks (tile, brick)? This then allows to check for collisions with blocks, which are otherwise disregarded due to performance.
        SVGData - The Collision Data for enemy.
        xPos - The x-Location of enemy.
        yPos - The y-Location of enemy.
        xVel - The x-Velocity of enemy.
        yVel - The y-Velocity of enemy.
        playerDeathSprites - Sprites to play player death animation (when Mario dies by this enemy).
        sprites - Sprites for Goomba's animations (0 and 1: For walking animation; 2: When Goomba dies by player).
